5-why root cause — cinematic black frame
1. The cinematic quality setting showed a blank scene because the post-processing output was not presented.
2. The base Three.js scene was healthy because the performance path, which bypassed post-processing, rendered correctly.
3. The optional composer stack was incompatible with the active renderer/browser integration.
4. That incompatibility blanked the whole scene because the enhancement layer sat in the critical presentation path.
5. Root cause: scene availability was coupled to an optional rendering enhancement.
Resolution: removed that coupling; the base renderer now owns presentation and the vignette is a non-critical CSS overlay.

5-why root cause — Pointer Lock launch failure
1. Mouse capture failed because the in-app Chromium surface rejected Pointer Lock.
2. The initial launch surfaced an error because the returned rejection was not handled.
3. The control design assumed Pointer Lock would always be available.
4. That assumption made mouse-look dependent on an optional browser capability.
5. Root cause: the primary navigation scheme lacked a capability-independent fallback.
Resolution: handle Pointer Lock rejection explicitly and provide canvas drag-to-look with the same WASD / vertical flight movement.
